reviewText: I liked the exer on this dvd - 3 different sections each about 20 minutes each-  When I start her workouts I always think, "this is too easy" however by the end I am feeling it! This DVD is a good addition to your collection/rotation. The only thing that is annoying is the fact she keeps saying "I have 4 kids" and Autumn has kids, No excuses! I liked her rapport better in 30 day slim down with her 'back up' girls but she gets the job done and you can turn off the instruction and only have music if you want- which in fact is some of the same exact music on Jillian Micheal's 30 Day Shred.
summary: great to target your tummy on "light" exercise days

reviewText: I love the variety in these 3 20-minute workouts!  I do not like working on my abs in the traditional way and these workouts are not that. Yes you will see some classics, but they are mixed in with some other great moves.  I love the pilates inspired section.  There is also a cardio workout which is more fun than difficult. Brooke has made workouts fresh and fun. Again this is beginner/immediate.  If you are advance you could use this on a day when you need a break from draining workouts.  I love all of her workouts and look forward to more.

reviewText: If you don't have a lot of time to work-out this is the dvd for you. Anyone can fit in 20 minutes a day. The moves are effective without being too hard.

reviewText: Reading other reviews led me to make this pruchase.  I enjoy this DVD and have used it almost every day since I got it.  Three workouts let you pick and choose, what you are in the mood for, or if you want to make a schedule for yourself.  The 1st one is sort of aeobic abs, the second is pilates inspired moves with more floor work, the last is "Sweet 16"...Brooke's 16 fav ab exercise--though not quite 16 because she count, left and right as two separate exercises.  For the most part, the exercise are suitableto begiiner/intermediate..Some are tougher than others, and I guess it depends on personal body strength.  I have more difficulty w exercises that work the lower abs, but obliques are easier for me.As a side note, which I addressed in my other review, did not see the Smoothie recipe.

reviewText: This DVD contains three workouts, of about 20 minutes each, for beginners to intermediate.  A light dumbbell or two are used occasionally.Here are the breakdowns.Cardio Crunch (0:20.01)Classic Core (0:19.28)Sweet 16 (0:20.07)1. Cardio Crunch:  This is the easiest of the three and the cardio, in general, is light and minimal.  The plie hop and the cardio can can are probably the two most intense cardio segments which you can easily modify.Warm up with stretches and light cardio(Standing work)Twisting pushRock punchStanding knee tuck, walkWaist carver to sideToe tapPlie hopCardio can canOblique twist(Floor work)Tap out plankPlank holdSwimmingTable top bridgeDolphinCool down with stretches2. Classic core (based on Pilates mat exercises)Warm up with stretches(Floor work)Rope climbTriple jacksOblique sweepLeg circleBridge kick(Standing work)3-count reach(Floor work)See saw crunchKnee tuckTriangle crunchBike SqueezeCool down with stretches3. Sweet 16: I liked (or hated) the Sweet 16 the most since it was the hardest or most intense of the three workouts.Warm up with light aerobics and stretchesAccordion crunchDead bugFull body rollClassic bicycleDumbbell twistAnkle crossRight triangleLeft triangleBridge toe tapSee saw obliqueBent knee windshieldCheek to cheekAb slamRight kick crunchLeft kick crunchOpen and closeCooldown with stretches
